Adult male.description: Adult male Connecticut Warblers have a complete eyering that adult male Mourning Warblers lack.

Immature.description: Immature Connecticut Warblers have a complete eyering whereas the eyering on immature Mourning Warblers looks broken. Also note the lack of a hooded look on Immature Connecticuts compared to immature Mourning Warblers. The throat on immature Connecticuts is often whitish rather than yellowish on Immature Mourning.

Adult male.description: Compared to female Mourning Warblers, Nashville Warblers have a yellow throat unlike the gray throated female Mourning Warblers. Nashville Warblers are also smaller and often more active.

Female/immature.description: Female/immature Nashville Warblers have a gray back whereas immature Mourning Warblers have a yellow-olive back. Also note size differences; Nashvilles are smaller and less bulky than Mourning Warblers.

Adult male.description: MacGillivray's Warblers have a broken eyering that Mourning Warblers lack. Also note that ranges do not overlap.
